                "invention-title": [
                    "SYSTEM AND METHOD FOR PLASMA GENERATION USING MICROWAVE",
                    "利用微波进行等离子体产生的系统和方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a plasma generator and a method of generating plasma. The electrodes in the reaction zone are excited by a high voltage power source electrically insulated from the electrodes. A first conductor array, preferably a coil, is electrically coupled to the power source and electrically insulated from the electrodes. A second conductor array, preferably a coaxial coil nested within the first conductor array, is electrically coupled to the electrode. Electromagnetic induction between the first conductor array and the second conductor array is used to excite the electrodes and generate a plasma in the reaction zone. One or more microwaves are further directed towards the plasma in parallel or in series to form a microwave plasma. Such plasma is used to reform a hydrocarbon feedstock to low C hydrocarbons, carbon or hydrogen. Further envisaged is a plasma generator that combines inductive plasma with tandem microwave plasma."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了等离子体发生器和产生等离子体的方法。反应区中的电极由与所述电极电绝缘的高压电源激励。第一导体阵列，优选地为线圈，电耦合至所述电源并且与所述电极电绝缘。第二导体阵列，优选地为嵌套在所述第一导体阵列内的同轴线圈，电耦合至所述电极。所述第一导体阵列与所述第二导体阵列之间的电磁感应用于激励所述电极并且在所述反应区中产生等离子体。进一步将一个或多个微波并联或串联地引导指向所述等离子体以形成微波等离子体。此类等离子体用于将烃原料重整为低C烃、碳或氢。进一步设想将感应等离子体与串联微波等离子体相结合的等离子体发生器。"
                }
            ]
